The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, May 12, 2004 				 Trinamul
																								Calcutta, May 11: Mamata Banerjee is waiting for a new government to be installed at the Centre to launch a save democracy campaign across the state.																								Even though the Election Commission took some decisions to ensure free and fair polls, the CPM-led government snatched the right of franchise from the people. We shall reach the people through a sustained movement demanding restoration of democracy in Bengal, Trinamul Congress spokesman and the leader of the Opposition in the Assembly, Pankaj Banerjee, said.
